Ask HN: Can we mount macOS clipboard as a filesystem?
text:
In the spirit of this [0] post on HN, I'm wondering if we can mount the clipboard contents as a drive on macOS. This can be super helpful when a website/application doesn't support drag-n-drop, but you want to select a screenshot as its input. Normally, you'd have to take the screenshot, then go to the website/app. It'll then open the file selector box/dialog where you can select the screenshot file. But if the clipboard was mounted as a drive, you wouldn't need to save the screenshot anymore—just take it and have it in the clipboard, then go to the website/app and select the image in the clipboard drive.

title: Ask HN: Drop your favorite mentorship orgs
text:
I've got a bunch of friends that are interested in starting their own enterprises but are having a hard time finding mentors. Right now the main sources of mentorship seem to be ondeck and y combinator, but these are for people who are interested in build tech stacks and apps - what if you want to start a spacetech company? or an online publishing company? or an online fitness co? All things that are going to integrate tech, but which don't actually fit into the ondeck/ycombinator model.

interested in seeing what you guys have come across..
